=begin
  gshunting4all.lic
  Universal hunting engine for GemStone IV (Lich 5) with GTK3 setup wizard.

  author: Falvicar
  game: Gemstone
  tags: hunting, combat, automate, society, arcarium, trinkets, gemstones, paladin, warrior, rogue, ranger, bard, cleric, empath, wizard, sorcerer
  required: Lich >= 5.9.0
  version: 2.0.2

  Usage:
    ;gshunting4all setup  -- open setup wizard
    ;gshunting4all        -- start hunting
    ;gshunting4all stop   -- stop the script
    In-game: PAUSE / RESUME

  NOT an AFK script -- you move between rooms, the script handles combat.
  Bugs / suggestions: Falvicar in-game or Discord: Shadowleaves

  Special thanks: Tysong and Hexbane for their help
  Dedicated to: Jaisey, Oogey, and Mandrill

  For version changelog notes, please see the changelog block by opening this with notepad.
=end

=begin
  changelog:
    2.0.2:
      Fixed holy weapon sense returning -1 (failure) when weapon is empty. Game
      response "nothing happens" was not in the dothistimeout pattern, so the call
      timed out and infuse_holy_weapon broke early (charges < 0 exit) before sending
      any PREP/INFUSE commands. Added "nothing happens" to the sense pattern and
      mapped it to return 0.
      Fixed encumbrance watcher sending "encumbrance" command while grouped. Check
      now skips entirely (no command, no hook) when group membership is detected.
      Simplified holy weapon management: refill only at hunt start, not mid-combat.
      On depletion the watcher sets @hw_depleted = true; beseech_holy_weapon returns
      early if set. Cleared at hunt start before infuse + beseech. Removed
      @hw_refilling and mid-combat Thread refill.
      Fixed BESEECH (1635) not firing when CC'd: mana_cost was 35, set to 0.
      Fixed script sending "prepare 1650" instead of BESEECH when incarnate armor
      path ran unconditionally alongside emergency_status abilities.
      Fixed low_health healing firing before wound retreat. Moved wound check to top
      of monitor_emergencies so escape always takes priority over healing.
      Fixed Energy Wings TURN missing target: verb now includes "at #TARGET".
      Fixed holy weapon beseech falsely triggering 30s backoff from warded-spell
      "nothing happens" bleeding into the beseech dothistimeout window.
    2.0.1:
      Fixed MG_ABILITIES uninitialized constant in pg_spell_rotation. Removed four
      non-existent trinket constants; kept only the five valid SCRIPT_TEMPLATES
      entries. Fixed gemstone/script sections using @saved_config instead of @profile.
    2.0.0:
      See git history for changes prior to 2.0.0.
      Grouped hunting overhaul: all retreat suppression (health, mana, overexerted,
      dread, encumbrance, navigation) now keys off actual group membership rather than
      the Grouped Mode master toggle. Eloot gating likewise uses real group detection.
      Fixed hidden-player hold blocking attacks when grouped rogues are hiding -- now
      uses named-player cross-check instead of unreliable pc.status inspection.
      Fixed group member cache storing "hidden" for hiding members ("who is hidden"
      suffix now stripped alongside "who is hiding" and "who is leading").
      Fixed eloot running with solo settings while grouped with toggle OFF.
      Fixed holy weapon double-beseech on per_attack mode. Fixed wound retreat while
      bound failing to fire Symbol of Return. Added "when" option legends to Scripts
      and CMANs tabs. Added Wound Retreat note clarifying per-part vs combo scoring.
      Replaced "Grouped mode: ON/OFF" startup line with actual group member list.
      Fixed hostile_npcs using stale GameObj.targets across room transitions;
      bosses that only attack via AOE/MDR (no <target> XML tag) now detected via
      boss-list scan of GameObj.npcs. Non-hostile town NPCs not on the boss list
      are never pulled in by either path.
      Detection code audit fixes: removed \bcoat\b from ARMOR_NOUNS (matched
      decorative coats as armor); replaced with coat\s+of so "coat of plates"
      matches but "long coat" does not. Flipped armor detection order to prefer
      GameObj.worn over weapon_inv_items so a worn chest piece always wins over
      any incidental armor-noun match in a container. Fixed bard sonic armor
      prompt text (said "press any key" but no keypress listener exists).
      Hoisted safe_containers out of the all_inv_items BFS loop so it is called
      once per detection pass instead of once per inventory item.
      Fixed vangaris arcarium showing aversaris vissi (and vice versa) due to
      output bleed between two sequential capture_detect calls. Root cause: the
      previous arcarium's analyze response arrives in-flight inside the next
      capture window, producing a concatenated output with both tables. Two-layer
      fix: (1) truncate captured lines to the LAST "You analyze the" marker so
      only the response belonging to our command is parsed; (2) stop at a second
      column-header table if both responses share the same marker position.
      Added a 1s pause between the two analyze calls to drain any in-flight
      server output before opening the next capture window.
      Fixed Holy Weapon auto-refill not firing reliably. The watcher hook
      (depletion message pattern) was the only trigger, which could miss or
      race with the combat loop. Added check_holy_weapon_charges which calls
      BESEECH SENSE between fights and refills proactively if charges are zero.
      This runs at the top of the maintenance block, before check_society_maintain,
      so the weapon is ready before society symbols fire. Watcher hook remains as
      a mid-combat backup. Sequence is: PREP <spell> then INFUSE my <noun>.
      Removed dead code: analyze_item_scripts (replaced by inline capture_detect
      calls), collect_store (replaced by collect_enabled_store), and _nb_prof
      local variable (computed but never read after a tab-building refactor).
      Fixed three DownstreamHook leaks on script stop: gsh4a_mount_cd_watcher,
      gsh4a_tech_cd_watcher, and gsh4a_dread_watcher had no stop methods and
      were never removed in the ensure block or before_dying. Added
      stop_mount_cd_watcher, stop_technique_cd_watcher, stop_dread_watcher, and
      wired all three plus stop_holy_weapon_watcher into both ensure and
      before_dying so hooks are always cleaned up regardless of how the script
      exits.
      Fixed weapon script detection missing weapons stored in backpacks and
      non-holder containers. Candidate scan now uses all_inv_items (full recursive
      inventory) instead of weapon_inv_items (weapon-holders-only); noun filter
      still limits to actual weapon/shield/armor nouns so non-equipment is skipped.
      Added plain \barmor\b to ARMOR_NOUNS so Bard Sonic Armor (noun: "armor") is
      detected. Added bard-specific prompt during detection: if no armor is found
      and the profession is Bard, detection pauses 3s so the bard can sing sonic
      armor first before the armor scan runs.
      Fixed Shield Specializations section showing CMans (Combat Focus, Combat
      Toughness, Cunning Defense, Dirtkick, etc.) instead of actual shield specs.
      Root cause: cman info detail calls (one per CMAN during detection) bleed
      their table output into the subsequent shield info capture window; those
      rows parse identically to shield spec rows. Fix: shield_specs detection now
      also filters out any mnemonic already present in the detected feats list.
      Fixed eloot running when a non-grouped player was already in the room on
      arrival: added 0.5s pause on room transition so GameObj.pcs is fully
      populated before stranger check; also fixed rescue true in run_eloot's
      stranger filter (now rescue false -- errors skip eloot rather than run it).
      Added explicit runestaff guard in the combat inner loop: fire_aoe_techniques
      and cmans_of_type("attack") are now skipped entirely for runestaff users
      (they have no weapon techniques or attack CMans and must not swing). Added
      spell_rotation_active? helper; mount_charge at engagement start is now
      suppressed when spell rotation is active (same suppression weapon rotation
      already had) to prevent double-fire if mount is slotted in the rotation.
      Expanded Spell Attack Rotation to support all non-melee ability types:
      mount charge/trample, arcarium vissi, trinket abilities, gemstone activations,
      and weapon/armor script abilities now appear in the Spell Attack Rotation
      dropdowns alongside spells. The rotation entry format is now identical to
      the Weapon Attack Rotation so fire_weapon_rot_entry handles all types for
      both paths. Simplified walk_rotation and run_aoe_phase to delegate to
      fire_weapon_rot_entry instead of duplicating type-dispatch logic.
      Renamed Attack Rotation tab to Weapon Attack Rotation. Added Spell Attack
      Rotation tab adjacent to it for pure casters using a runestaff. The Spell
      Attack Rotation tab is hidden when the primary weapon is not a runestaff;
      the Weapon Attack Rotation tab is hidden when it is. Moved the single-target
      and AoE spell rotation frames from the Spells tab into the Spell Attack
      Rotation tab. Hybrid classes continue to use the Weapon Attack Rotation to
      interleave spells and weapon abilities as before. Updated all in-tab notes
      and grayout labels across Scripts, Defense, Mount, Warrior Guild, Arcarium,
      Trinkets, Gemstones, Society, and Character tabs to say Weapon Attack
      Rotation instead of Attack Rotation.
      Removed dead data: d[:uac_hands] and d[:uac_feet] were assigned during
      detection but never read by any downstream code; removed both assignments.
      Fixed cman detail call bleed: added 0.3s inter-call pause before each
      "cman info <name>" capture_detect and increased timeout from 1.5s to 3.0s
      so server output from the previous detail page fully drains before the next
      capture window opens.
      Fixed detect_known_spells silent-zero edge case: if Lich's spell cache
      returns empty for a profession that should know spells (not warrior/rogue/
      monk), detection now logs a user-visible warning suggesting they re-run
      the script after the game XML stream has fully settled post-login.
      Fixed pg_spell_rotation uninitialized constant error: trinket_defs
      referenced MG_ABILITIES, MAGIC_GLOVES_ABILITIES, MANA_BATTERY_ABILITIES,
      and BSJ_ABILITIES which do not exist. Reduced to the five slots that have
      actual constants (Energy Wings, Battle Standard, Elemental/Twisted Gloves,
      Twisted Kicks). Fixed gemstone and script sections using @saved_config
      instead of @profile (matching pg_combat_abilities exactly).

=end

require 'yaml'
require 'fileutils'
require 'set'

# All script internals live inside this module -- no global namespace pollution.
module GSH4A

SCRIPT_VERSION = "2.0.8".freeze
PROFILE_DIR = File.join(File.dirname(__FILE__), "gsh4a_profiles")
FileUtils.mkdir_p(PROFILE_DIR)

CASTER_NOUNS = %w[
  conjurer mage wizard necromancer shaman priest sorcerer warlock
  channeler ritualist arcanist scholar sage invoker summoner adept
].freeze

# Named rare spawns listed on the GemStone IV wiki as "Miniboss" type,
# plus all Reim rares (Castle + Fortress). Used when "Count Mini Bosses as bosses" is enabled.
MINIBOSS_NAMES = [
  "psionicist", "dogmatist", "goleras", "skayl", "dybbuk", "vesperti", "fenghai", "siren",
  "triton warden", "triton fanatic", "triton protector", "triton brawler",
  "triton warlock", "greater construct", "illoke elder", "vvrael warlock", "vvrael witch",
  "raving lunatic", "fire mage", "muscular supplicant", "black forest ogre", "massive pyrothag",
  "stone troll", "tomb troll", "greater faeroth", "kiramon defender", "forest trali shaman",
  "bog wight", "night mare", "frozen corpse", "spectral miner", "greater bog troll",
  "krolvin corsair", "troll wraith", "lava troll", "moor witch", "hisskra chieftain",
  "hisskra shaman", "ash hag", "krolvin warfarer", "arachne priest", "centaur",
  # Reim Castle rares (empress/emperor handled by their own checkboxes)
  "shopkeeper", "innkeeper", "bartender", "patrol leader",
  "bandit lord", "bandit lady", "gypsy queen", "gypsy king",
  "guard captain", "wall captain", "drill sergeant", "hostler", "dungeon master",
  "butler", "cook", "knight captain", "dignitary", "princess", "prince", "jester",
  # Fortress of Reim rares
  "massive butcher", "tower-shielded sentinel", "hulking vanguard", "fanatical executioner",
  "torturer", "slender mercenary", "assassin", "stealthy scout",
  "highwayman", "skirmisher", "darkly hooded figure", "sinister necromancer",
  "occult ritualist", "shadow-weaving sorcerer", "plagued defiler", "towering crusader",
  "heavy-armored paladin", "resolute knight", "warpriest", "scarred champion"
].freeze

# Nouns/names that must never be attacked -- town authority and non-hostile NPCs.
# Checked against both NPC noun and full name so partial matches (e.g. "town guard") are caught.
GIGAS_PATTERN = /\bgigas\b/i.freeze

SAFE_NPC_PATTERN = /\b(
  guard|constable|sheriff|marshal|marshall|deputy|watchman|watch|
  militia|militiaman|bailiff|magistrate|judge|warden|enforcer|
  captain|lieutenant|sergeant|corporal|officer|soldier|sentinel|
  alderman|councilor|chancellor|steward|herald|emissary|envoy|
  banker|clerk|shopkeeper|merchant|vendor|innkeeper|bartender|
  healer|herbalist|townsfolk|citizen|commoner|peasant|beggar|
  child|infant|baby|youth|elder|grandmother|grandfather
)\b/xi.freeze


REJECT_PATTERN = /recently|cannot|not yet|too soon|does not respond|no effect|still in cooldown|already used|connection to the other valence has diminished/i

# Rooms where combat must never happen regardless of what wanders in.
# Script holds attacks and skips eloot until it naturally moves on.
SANCTUARY_ROOMS = [
  32469,  # Moonsedge Castle, Library (fireplace alcove) -- sanctuary; beasties occasionally wander in
].freeze

# Body parts for per-part wound retreat config.
# Each entry: [config_key, Wounds_method, display_label, default_threshold]
# default_threshold 0 = disabled for that part by default.
WOUND_BODY_PARTS = [
  # Row 0: head area + nerves
  ["head",      :head,      "Head",       2],
  ["neck",      :neck,      "Neck",       2],
  ["rightEye",  :rightEye,  "Right Eye",  0],
  ["leftEye",   :leftEye,   "Left Eye",   0],
  ["nerves",    :nerves,    "Nerves",     2],
  # Row 1: torso + upper limbs
  ["chest",     :chest,     "Chest",      2],
  ["back",      :back,      "Back",       2],
  ["abdomen",   :abdomen,   "Abdomen",    2],
  ["rightArm",  :rightArm,  "Right Arm",  3],
  ["leftArm",   :leftArm,   "Left Arm",   3],
  # Row 2: hands + legs (4 items, last column empty)
  ["rightHand", :rightHand, "Right Hand", 3],
  ["leftHand",  :leftHand,  "Left Hand",  3],
  ["rightLeg",  :rightLeg,  "Right Leg",  3],
  ["leftLeg",   :leftLeg,   "Left Leg",   3],
].freeze

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SCRIPT ABILITY TEMPLATES
# #NOUN is replaced with the item noun at profile save time.
# #TARGET is replaced at runtime with the enemy's ID.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
SCRIPT_TEMPLATES = {
